00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:51,750
Hello, Boris. What's up?

264
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:55,180
Where are you? Why didn't you come here to practice?

265
00:21:55,180 --> 00:21:59,370
Boris, you saw the topic too. It's fermentation.

266
00:21:59,370 --> 00:22:02,190
If you want me to ferment wine or vinegar,

267
00:22:02,190 --> 00:22:05,470
pickles, leaven dough, just let me be.

268
00:22:05,470 --> 00:22:09,430
I've been dealing with these things since childhood. Let me get some fresh air.

269
00:22:09,430 --> 00:22:12,450
Let me relax, and then I can welcome better challenges. Isn't that right?

270
00:22:12,450 --> 00:22:14,350
Get fresh air?

271
00:22:14,350 --> 00:22:19,970
On the battlefield, you tell the enemy, "Wait.

272
00:22:19,970 --> 00:22:21,630
I want to get some fresh air.

273
00:22:21,630 --> 00:22:25,960
I'll fight when I'm ready." What are you doing? Are you kidding me?

274
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:29,540
- Are you insane?
 - Okay, okay.

275
00:22:29,540 --> 00:22:32,960
I can practice by myself. Besides, after two rounds of the competition,

276
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:35,200
the situation is already clear.

277
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:40,130
Only Victor needs to be taken seriously. Relax a little, Boris. Bye.

278
00:22:40,130 --> 00:22:43,130
You...

279
00:22:43,130 --> 00:22:46,370
Watch how I will deal with you!

280
00:22:46,370 --> 00:22:49,870
You must come back here in five minutes!

281
00:22:52,090 --> 00:22:55,000
Is it really okay that you hanged up on him like that?

282
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:58,300
Have you finished drawing? Let me see it.

283
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:00,920
Here!

284
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:06,250
Hello Kitty?

285
00:23:06,250 --> 00:23:09,060
Let me draw it.

286
00:23:13,150 --> 00:23:16,580
Now you look like Hello Kitty.

287
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:19,630
Do I?

288
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:27,170
Elise, you sure took a while to chat?

289
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:32,470
Mom. I was only...

290
00:23:32,470 --> 00:23:34,140
Elise, you're finally back.

291
00:23:34,140 --> 00:23:36,610
Hurry and taste it. Give me a score.

292
00:23:36,610 --> 00:23:38,760
It looks good.

293
00:23:43,260 --> 00:23:45,790
Excellent. It's much better than Lin Kesong's.

294
00:23:45,790 --> 00:23:49,010
I taught her all morning, but she still made a mess.

295
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:52,670
What? Did you go to teach Lin Kesong?

296
00:23:52,670 --> 00:23:56,450
Why? You promised me.

297
00:23:56,450 --> 00:24:00,280
Sorry. It's Oliver who...

298
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:06,860
So, in your mind,

299
00:24:06,860 --> 00:24:09,890
what your ex-boyfriend says means more than what your mother says?

300
00:24:09,890 --> 00:24:14,470
Your ex-boyfriend's apprentice is more important than your own brother?

301
00:24:18,070 --> 00:24:21,880
It's not that. Even if Lin Kesong learns it, she still won't be better than Victor.

302
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:24,340
Why didn't you refuse?

303
00:24:26,410 --> 00:24:30,240
Mom, it's already done, so it's useless to speak about it any further,

304
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:35,100
but I don't want to learn the same thing as Lin Kesong does. She's not qualified.

305
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:37,820
I will cook three different fermented dishes right now.

306
00:24:37,820 --> 00:24:40,420
Mom, see you in a while.

307
00:24:43,860 --> 00:24:46,450
You've really disappointed me.

308
00:24:50,650 --> 00:24:52,850
Sorry, Mom.

309
00:24:52,850 --> 00:24:54,730
Where are you going in a while?

310
00:24:54,730 --> 00:24:57,370
I haven't thought about it.

311
00:24:57,370 --> 00:24:59,320
- Da Mai.
- Da Mai.

312
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,570
Yours.

313
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:11,020
Rheumatoid arthritis?

314
00:25:11,020 --> 00:25:12,580
What's yours?

315
00:25:12,580 --> 00:25:16,260
Mine too. We both have rheumatoid arthritis. Isn't this too fake?

316
00:25:16,260 --> 00:25:18,790
Why so much useless talk?

317
00:25:18,790 --> 00:25:20,990
I also have rheumatoid arthritis.

318
00:25:20,990 --> 00:25:23,220
Let me tell you.

319
00:25:23,220 --> 00:25:26,740
This is not for them to believe.

320
00:25:26,740 --> 00:25:30,530
It's to let them know clearly but they can't say anything.

321
00:25:30,530 --> 00:25:33,430
Blocking. Get it?

322
00:25:34,530 --> 00:25:38,510
Let me tell you. Treat today as if it's the last day.

323
00:25:38,510 --> 00:25:39,810
Don't make it easy for them.

324
00:25:39,810 --> 00:25:41,090
Sure, we'll do what you say.

325
00:25:41,090 --> 00:25:43,030
- Go on.
- Yes. Go.

326
00:26:38,390 --> 00:26:40,340
[Express Delivery]

327
00:26:48,350 --> 00:26:52,310
[Dear Mr Jiang. Hello. You don't need to know who I am...]

328
00:26:52,310 --> 00:26:56,280
[But there's something you need to know.]

329
00:26:59,630 --> 00:27:01,880
An anonymous letter.

330
00:27:10,460 --> 00:27:12,890
Oliver, I received an anonymous letter.

331
00:27:12,890 --> 00:27:15,200
It says people in the kitchen are planning a walkout.

332
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:19,020
It's probably Da Mai, but not just him. What do we do?

333
00:27:38,060 --> 00:27:41,280
Okay. We just received a batch of small wheat melons today.

334
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:45,560
The quality is excellent, very fresh. You can recommend them to the customers.

335
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:49,760
And then, everyone did a great job yesterday. Especially the floor in the front,

336
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:52,440
all the corners are particularly clean.

337
00:27:54,370 --> 00:27:57,830
Da Mai, take off the apron.

338
00:27:59,420 --> 00:28:01,860
- Why?
- Go back to the kitchen.

339
00:28:01,860 --> 00:28:03,160
Everyone else, meeting dismissed.

340
00:28:03,160 --> 00:28:04,720
Wait.

341
00:28:05,870 --> 00:28:10,420
Mr. Jiang, I can go back to the kitchen, but at least give us an explanation.

342
00:28:10,420 --> 00:28:15,940
You can't just make me wash vegetables whenever you say, or make me go back to the kitchen anytime. You make everyone feel unsettled. How can we do the job?

343
00:28:15,940 --> 00:28:19,130
It's been quite a few days. You still don't know what mistake you made?

344
00:28:19,130 --> 00:28:22,450
You tell me then. Let me see if it's the same as I thought.

345
00:28:22,450 --> 00:28:25,890
Number 8 in the management rules, daily meetings start at 5 pm every afternoon.

346
00:28:25,890 --> 00:28:29,550
Staff on duty cannot be late. Have you forgotten?

347
00:28:31,540 --> 00:28:36,130
So it's because I was late for the meeting.

348
00:28:36,130 --> 00:28:39,350
I thought it was because someone was narrow-minded,

349
00:28:39,350 --> 00:28:44,030
and couldn't accept that I said his Wagyu SIrloin and Red Crayfish didn't taste good.

350
00:28:44,030 --> 00:28:46,590
Da Mai, Mr. Jiang has already explained the reason.

351
00:28:46,590 --> 00:28:49,590
You know now. Okay, everyone, let's get to work.

352
00:28:49,590 --> 00:28:51,210
Wait.

353
00:28:53,150 --> 00:28:56,020
The Wagyu Sirloin and Red Crayfish dish,

354
00:28:56,020 --> 00:29:00,500
everyone has tried it. Other than Da Mai,

355
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:03,100
does anyone think it doesn't taste good?

356
00:29:04,330 --> 00:29:06,960
Mr. Jiang,

357
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:09,650
whatever you cook is the standard.

358
00:29:09,650 --> 00:29:13,630
We... We don't dare to have any.

359
00:29:13,630 --> 00:29:17,760
Does anyone think it tastes bad? Just raise your hand to show me.

360
00:29:25,850 --> 00:29:30,090
Mr. Jiang has spoken. You've all eaten that dish.

361
00:29:32,130 --> 00:29:33,910
Anyone else?

362
00:29:34,960 --> 00:29:37,020
Sorry, Mr. Jiang.

363
00:29:38,930 --> 00:29:41,010
I think it tastes good.

364
00:29:44,450 --> 00:29:46,080
Sorry.

365
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:50,620
I also think it's not good.

366
00:29:53,830 --> 00:29:58,390
Even though Yuxuan is mine, it also belongs to everyone here.

367
00:29:58,390 --> 00:30:00,500
Everyone is equal when it comes to the quality of food.

368
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:03,380
I will withdraw this dish.

369
00:30:03,380 --> 00:30:08,380
Next, I will work hard to develop new dishes, so everyone can go back to work.

370
00:30:08,380 --> 00:30:10,370
Dismissed.

371
00:30:12,780 --> 00:30:14,760
What's going on?

372
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:17,520
- What's happening?
- What's going on?

373
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:20,100
Haven't you heard what Mr. Jiang said?

374
00:30:20,100 --> 00:30:23,210
Go back to work. Why are you standing here dazed?

375
00:30:23,210 --> 00:30:25,430
Go. Go. Go.

376
00:30:25,430 --> 00:30:28,720
I didn't know you would surrender.

377
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:31,010
Half of what I said is true.

378
00:30:31,010 --> 00:30:34,780
The most important thing now is to stabilize Yuxuan's kitchen.

379
00:30:34,780 --> 00:30:39,330
That was hard on you. If the lead chef and the two assistant chefs were really leaving,

380
00:30:39,330 --> 00:30:42,080
the kitchen would suddenly lose three people. That's big trouble.

381
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:46,680
You are right. We haven't even gotten Michelin's third star,

382
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:50,010
we can't let Yuxuan become unstable,

383
00:30:50,010 --> 00:30:52,370
but how did you know about this matter?

384
00:30:57,950 --> 00:30:59,820
This is the anonymous letter.

385
00:31:02,900 --> 00:31:04,100
Read this paragraph.

386
00:31:04,100 --> 00:31:08,070
There is already resistance among the crew. It will definitely develop other conflicts.

387
00:31:08,070 --> 00:31:12,140
It can be quite a blow to Yuxuan's plan to get the three stars.

388
00:31:12,140 --> 00:31:13,920
That's exactly the problem.

389
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:15,900
Develop what other conflicts?

390
00:31:15,900 --> 00:31:18,860
Who knew about this incident?

391
00:31:18,860 --> 00:31:21,520
- When did you find out?
- This morning.

392
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:24,030
It was by a one-hour express delivery.

393
00:31:24,030 --> 00:31:28,510
Why such a rush? The writer of the letter wanted us to see it before the pre-shift meeting.

394
00:31:28,510 --> 00:31:30,790
Luckily, you are here.

395
00:31:30,790 --> 00:31:32,420
There's another matter.

396
00:31:32,420 --> 00:31:34,640
A restaurant headhunter came to me a few days ago.

397
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:38,230
He beat around the bush to ask me whether Yuxuan's staff were changing.

398
00:31:38,230 --> 00:31:41,410
If there is an employee who didn't want to renew, I could recommend them to him. Anyone from here,

399
00:31:41,410 --> 00:31:43,700
at any position, he would rush to have them.

400
00:31:43,700 --> 00:31:47,050
I was curious about it. It all matches now with this letter.

401
00:31:47,050 --> 00:31:48,930
Someone is making trouble,

402
00:31:48,930 --> 00:31:51,930
and they've already lined up the next restaurant. The headhunter saw the resume.

403
00:31:51,930 --> 00:31:55,840
So someone thought we wanted to cut down the staff and rushed to grab them.

404
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:58,770
Something was quite interesting just now.

405
00:31:58,770 --> 00:32:03,220
You said they wanted to get anyone at any position? That means it's not just the kitchen.

406
00:32:03,220 --> 00:32:05,960
This person must be very knowledgeable about our internal situation.

407
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:10,140
Elise, pay attention to the manager. He must know about it.

408
00:32:10,140 --> 00:32:11,540
Okay.

409
00:32:15,690 --> 00:32:17,690
I'll go check the kitchen first.

410
00:32:24,300 --> 00:32:27,740
Da Mai, do we leave or not?

411
00:32:28,460 --> 00:32:29,820
Well?

412
00:32:32,850 --> 00:32:34,390
What's the situation?

413
00:32:36,230 --> 00:32:38,340
Let me ask you.

414
00:32:38,340 --> 00:32:42,870
Did Jiang Qianfan voluntarily withdraw his dish this time?

415
00:32:42,870 --> 00:32:44,410
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

416
00:32:44,410 --> 00:32:49,130
Jiang Qianfan voluntarily admitted his mistake. Isn't it the first time in Yuxuan?

417
00:32:49,130 --> 00:32:51,330
- Yeah, it's the first time.
- Right.

418
00:32:51,330 --> 00:32:54,080
Doesn't this mean that I've

419
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:57,280
won a total victory on this matter?

420
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:59,890
Yes. Yes.

421
00:32:59,890 --> 00:33:01,120
Why should we leave then?

422
00:33:01,120 --> 00:33:02,970
So we're not leaving?

423
00:33:02,970 --> 00:33:05,660
- Not leaving then?
- Give me the sick-leave note.

424
00:33:09,090 --> 00:33:11,760
Tear them up.

425
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:14,260
We won. Why are we leaving?

426
00:33:17,990 --> 00:33:20,550
See? The fence-sitter.

427
00:33:20,550 --> 00:33:23,270
- He's calling.
- Let's see what he says.

428
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:27,530
- Who's that?
- What's going on with you?

429
00:33:27,530 --> 00:33:30,070
You've already signed their contract.

430
00:33:30,070 --> 00:33:32,470
Manager?

431
00:33:32,470 --> 00:33:35,810
What did you say? I was going to ask you something.

432
00:33:35,810 --> 00:33:40,650
Do you think the Wagyu Sirloin and Red Crayfish taste good?

433
00:33:40,650 --> 00:33:41,720
What do you mean?

434
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:45,890
I remember when we were giving our opinion, someone didn't raise his hand.

435
00:33:45,890 --> 00:33:50,570
I saw everyone else had raised their hand, mine wasn't needed.

436
00:33:50,570 --> 00:33:54,380
That's why they say you don't know someone unless you go through trouble together.

437
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:57,860
You are really fast to change sides. Okay.

438
00:33:57,860 --> 00:34:02,260
I'll wish you to have a bright future. Bye-bye.

439
00:34:03,250 --> 00:34:04,730
Fence-sitter. What is he?

440
00:34:04,730 --> 00:34:06,560
- That's right.
- That's enough. Hurry and tidy up.

441
00:34:06,560 --> 00:34:08,790
- Let's get to work.
- Okay.

442
00:34:11,580 --> 00:34:13,510
Traitor.

443
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:27,220
Old Zhou, your level is not bad.

444
00:34:27,220 --> 00:34:30,350
- You have the potential to be the lead chef.
- Brother Mai, you're back.

445
00:34:30,350 --> 00:34:33,150
- Go take a break.
- You do it.

446
00:34:38,190 --> 00:34:41,030
Xiao Pa, come here.

447
00:34:45,620 --> 00:34:47,040
[Express Delivery]

448
00:34:48,540 --> 00:34:50,980
Have a seat.

449
00:35:02,710 --> 00:35:04,780
Xiao Pa.

450
00:35:04,780 --> 00:35:07,540
You were hired when Yuxuan was first established in Shanghai, right?

451
00:35:07,540 --> 00:35:09,090
Yes.

452
00:35:15,940 --> 00:35:20,250
A few in the front were brought in by me from London. How well do you get along?

453
00:35:21,030 --> 00:35:22,790
These few are seniors.

454
00:35:22,790 --> 00:35:26,720
They are more experienced, so I try to learn from them.

455
00:35:26,720 --> 00:35:28,880
Why are you asking about this?

456
00:35:29,790 --> 00:35:32,400
I've been self-reflecting about Da Mai.

457
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:33,670
I am responsible too.

458
00:35:33,670 --> 00:35:36,410
I didn't give your suggestions to Mr. Jiang in time.

459
00:35:36,410 --> 00:35:40,120
If something similar happens again, what do you think about collecting everyone's suggestions?

460
00:35:40,120 --> 00:35:43,650
Mr. Jiang is an artist for the tip of the tongue.

461
00:35:43,650 --> 00:35:45,680
You take care of his feelings.

462
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:48,590
I can understand you're afraid of hurting his sensitive feelings,

463
00:35:48,590 --> 00:35:52,570
but have you ever thought the customers are concerned about this?

464
00:35:52,570 --> 00:35:54,820
Our restaurant's customers are all high caliber.

465
00:35:54,820 --> 00:35:57,360
Other than Boris, everyone else was too shy to give an opinion.

466
00:35:57,360 --> 00:35:59,540
We're all afraid of sounding unprofessional,

467
00:35:59,540 --> 00:36:02,890
so when you and the manager ask us for our opinions,

468
00:36:02,890 --> 00:36:06,390
I don't think you'd hear much truth.

469
00:36:06,390 --> 00:36:09,490
Then, do you have any solution?

470
00:36:10,310 --> 00:36:13,610
Previously, I worked in a western-style restaurant in the Huangpu District.

471
00:36:13,610 --> 00:36:17,270
They use a method where they

472
00:36:17,270 --> 00:36:20,900
listed likable dishes and disliked dishes on the same questionnaire.

473
00:36:20,900 --> 00:36:23,540
Just let people place a check mark. It's completely anonymous.

474
00:36:23,540 --> 00:36:25,860
This way, no one is afraid to offend anyone.

475
00:36:25,860 --> 00:36:28,500
The restaurant will give them a small gift,

476
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:31,360
such as a paper folded animal.

477
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:34,920
The customers were all happy. Do you think this is a good way?

478
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:36,690
It is good.

479
00:36:36,690 --> 00:36:40,010
Then, what about when the staff has a bad mood?

480
00:36:42,100 --> 00:36:43,920
Sorry, Miss Quentin.

481
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:47,850
I'll be bold and say this.

482
00:36:47,850 --> 00:36:49,190
You know.

483
00:36:49,190 --> 00:36:51,810
If you wait for the staff to tell you their opinions,

484
00:36:51,810 --> 00:36:54,040
it means there is already an internal conflict that's getting strong.

485
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:55,710
There's already big trouble.

486
00:36:55,710 --> 00:36:59,700
That's why if you want to protect Mr. Jiang, you should tell him the truth

487
00:36:59,700 --> 00:37:02,970
because I think Mr. Jiang is the most talented chef.

488
00:37:02,970 --> 00:37:06,360
If he knows the truth, he will definitely find a solution.

489
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:10,310
Isn't this another method to protect the Yuxuan restaurant?

490
00:37:10,310 --> 00:37:11,480
That's right.

491
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:12,840
Thank you, Xiao Pa.

492
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:14,900
I didn't know you love Yuxuan so much.

493
00:37:14,900 --> 00:37:16,780
I have one last question.

494
00:37:16,780 --> 00:37:21,050
Do you think the management rules should be improved?

495
00:37:25,770 --> 00:37:27,040
Not yet for now,

496
00:37:27,040 --> 00:37:29,420
but I think there definitely will be in the future.

497
00:37:29,420 --> 00:37:32,480
If you want to hear about it, I'll come to you to tell you.

498
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:34,540
There definitely will be?

499
00:37:34,540 --> 00:37:37,170
You are misunderstanding what I'm saying.

500
00:37:37,170 --> 00:37:41,280
I meant, that even the best system can't meet situational changes.

501
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:44,440
When we encounter a new situation, we'll resolve it with a new system.

502
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:46,880
A living system is the best system.

503
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:50,120
It's hopeless to stand by an inflexible rule.

504
00:37:51,660 --> 00:37:55,780
Miss Quentin, I don't know why I have been so talkative today.

505
00:37:55,780 --> 00:37:58,250
No, no. It's really excellent, Xiao Pa.

506
00:37:58,250 --> 00:38:00,510
Thank you very much. You can get back to work.

507
00:38:00,510 --> 00:38:02,180
You are being courteous.

508
00:38:08,600 --> 00:38:11,310
Xiao Pa, come here.

509
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:16,200
- Manager.
- What was Elise talking to you about?

510
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:18,930
She was asking me how to get customers' opinions.

511
00:38:21,430 --> 00:38:23,640
Nothing else?

512
00:38:23,640 --> 00:38:26,780
Don't worry. I didn't say anything about that.

513
00:38:26,780 --> 00:38:28,820
Good. Good.

514
00:38:28,820 --> 00:38:30,440
Go to work then.

515
00:39:03,410 --> 00:39:05,540
